CS:GO is much less a game and more-so a sport now. It's frustrating at times, sometimes has RNG elements, but it's also very intense and allows me to get excited. I'm still not very good at the game in comparison to the rest of the player base, but I can still make some sick plays.

It takes some learning to understand how to play the game and the develop the skills necessary to co-ordinate your team and work tactically, but it's worth it. :)
